=== Justfile ===
# snap-project — Cardano protocol project
# Generated by cardano-init. Edit freely.

default:
    @just --list

# --- On-chain (Aiken) ---
build-on-chain:
    just -f on-chain/Justfile build

test-on-chain:
    just -f on-chain/Justfile test

# --- Off-chain (MeshJS) ---
build-off-chain:
    just -f off-chain/Justfile build

test-off-chain:
    just -f off-chain/Justfile test

# --- Aggregate tasks ---
build: build-on-chain build-off-chain
    @echo "Build complete."

test: test-on-chain test-off-chain
    @echo "All tests passed."

clean:
    just -f on-chain/Justfile clean
    just -f off-chain/Justfile clean
    rm -f blueprint/plutus.json
    @echo "Clean complete."

# --- dev: bring up the shared, long-running infrastructure ---
# Per-component watch/dev (on-chain, off-chain, testing, formal-methods) is run
# directly in each component dir; only infrastructure is orchestrated here.
dev:
    @echo "No infrastructure to start. Run a component's dev directly:"
    @echo "  just -f on-chain/Justfile dev"
    @echo "  just -f off-chain/Justfile dev"

=== README.md ===
# snap-project

A Cardano protocol project generated by [cardano-init](https://github.com/aspect-build/cardano-init).

## Architecture

```
snap-project/
├── Justfile                    # Task orchestration
├── on-chain/                  # Aiken (aiken)
├── off-chain/                 # MeshJS (typescript)
├── blueprint/                  # CIP-57 Plutus blueprint (drop or build plutus.json here)
└── README.md
```

## Quick Start

```bash
just build    # Build all components
just test     # Run all tests
just clean    # Remove build artifacts
```

## On-chain: Aiken

The `on-chain/` directory contains the smart contract logic written in aiken.

```bash
just build-on-chain
just test-on-chain
```

## Off-chain: MeshJS

The `off-chain/` directory contains the transaction building and submission logic written in typescript.

```bash
just build-off-chain
just test-off-chain
```

## Network

This project targets the **preprod** network.

